  "interpretation": [
    "Raw Alpaca-news proximity is too broad: 147/152 abnormal windows had prior/same-day PIT news, so simple news proximity cannot separate useful event-risk amplification from ordinary news saturation.",
    "Overall PIT-news-proximate option abnormality did not show a robust incremental edge versus matched controls: 10d path-range delta was about -0.08 percentage points and 10d directional delta about -0.16 percentage points.",
    "Event family matters more than raw proximity. Earnings/guidance-family windows were the strongest small slice: 20 windows across 4 symbols with 10d absolute-return delta about +3.08 percentage points and 10d path-range delta about +1.47 percentage points versus controls.",
    "General company news was negative versus controls, so treating all news as equal dilutes any event-risk effect.",
    "The result supports the next architecture direction: option abnormality may be useful as an event-risk amplifier only after event interpretation classifies materiality, lifecycle, surprise/known-vs-unknown status, and family. Raw option abnormality + raw news proximity still should not be promoted."
  ],
